.TH "SEED\-CLI" "1" "February 2026" "0.1.1" "Seed Hypermedia"
.SH "NAME"
\fBseed-cli\fR \- interact with the Seed Hypermedia network
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBseed\-cli\fP [global\-options] <command> [command\-options]
.P
\fBseed\-cli\fP document get <id> [\-\-md] [\-\-resolve] \fBseed\-cli\fP document create <account> \-\-body\-file <file> \-\-key <key>
.br
\fBseed\-cli\fP document update <id> \-\-replace\-body <file> \-\-key <key> \fBseed\-cli\fP comment create <target> \-\-body <text> \-\-key
.br
<key> \fBseed\-cli\fP comment edit <commentId> \-\-body <text> \-\-key <key> \fBseed\-cli\fP account list \fBseed\-cli\fP key generate
.br
\-\-name <name> \-\-show\-mnemonic
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBseed\-cli\fP is a command\-line interface for interacting with the Seed Hypermedia network\. It queries documents, manages
.br
accounts, searches content, creates and updates documents, posts comments, and manages cryptographic signing keys\.
.P
Seed servers are open\-source, self\-hostable nodes on a peer\-to\-peer hypermedia network\. Every piece of content is
.br
identified by a Hypermedia ID (\fBhm://\fP), signed with Ed25519 keys, and stored as content\-addressed CBOR blobs\. The CLI
.br
communicates with any Seed server over its HTTP API\.
.P
Source code: https://github.com/seed-hypermedia/seed Website: https://seed.hyper.media
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-s\fP, \fB\-\-server\fP <url>: Server URL\. Default: \fBhttps://hyper\.media\fP\|\. Override per session with the \fBSEED_SERVER\fP
.br
environment variable\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-json\fP: JSON output (default)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-yaml\fP: YAML output\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-pretty\fP: Pretty\-printed JSON output\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Minimal output\. Typically prints one value per line, tab\-separated\. Useful for scripting\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-dev\fP: Use the development keyring (\fBseed\-daemon\-dev\fP) instead of the production keyring (\fBseed\-daemon\-main\fP)\. Keys
.br
are shared with the local Seed desktop daemon\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-V\fP, \fB\-\-version\fP: Print version number and exit\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP: Print help text and exit\.

.RE
.SH HYPERMEDIA ID FORMAT
.P
Seed uses Hypermedia IDs to reference all content:
.RS 2
.nf
hm://<account>[/<path>][?v=<version>][#<block\-ref>]
.fi
.RE

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<account>\fP: A base58btc\-encoded Ed25519 public key, starting with \fBz6Mk\fP\|\. Identifies the owner/space\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<path>\fP: Optional slash\-separated path segments\. Documents form a tree under each account: \fB/\fP is the home document,
.br
\fB/projects\fP is a child, \fB/projects/alpha\fP is a grandchild\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB?v=<version>\fP: Optional version CID (\fBbafy2bz\.\.\.\fP)\. Pins the reference to a specific document version\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB#<block\-ref>\fP: Optional block ID\. References a specific block within the document\. Used for block\-level comments and
.br
citations\.

.RE
.P
Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
hm://z6MkrbYs\.\.\.
hm://z6MkrbYs\.\.\./projects/alpha
hm://z6MkrbYs\.\.\./projects/alpha?v=bafy2bzace\.\.\.
hm://z6MkrbYs\.\.\./projects/alpha#Urol\-mKf
.fi
.RE
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Document Operations
.SS document get <id>
.P
Fetch a document by Hypermedia ID and display its content\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-m\fP, \fB\-\-metadata\fP: Fetch metadata only (title, summary, icon)\. Faster than full fetch\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-md\fP: Output as GitHub\-flavored Markdown\. Headings, bold, italic, code, links, images, embeds, and queries are all
.br
converted\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-frontmatter\fP: Include YAML frontmatter with document metadata (use with \fB\-\-md\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-r\fP, \fB\-\-resolve\fP: Resolve embedded documents and queries inline (use with \fB\-\-md\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Print only the document title (or ID if untitled)\.

.RE
.P
Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./blog/post" \-\-md
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\." \-\-md \-\-resolve \-\-frontmatter
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\.?v=bafy\.\.\." \-\-json
.fi
.RE
.SS document create <account>
.P
Create a new document from Markdown content\. This is the "genesis trick": the CLI creates three signed CBOR blobs in
.br
sequence:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBGenesis change\fR \-\- the document's immutable identity anchor\. Its CID is computed from the signed blob (which
.br
includes the signer's public key), cryptographically binding the document identity to the creating key\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBDocument change\fR \-\- contains the actual content operations (SetAttributes for title, ReplaceBlock + MoveBlocks for
.br
each content block), referencing genesis as both parent and dependency\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBRef\fR \-\- a version pointer linking the genesis to a path under the target account space\.

.RE
.P
The server stores the genesis first, then the change and ref that reference it\. After creation the document is
.br
immediately accessible at \fBhm://<account>/<path>\fP\|\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-p\fP, \fB\-\-path\fP <path>: Document path (e\.g\. \fBmy\-document\fP)\. Auto\-generated from title if omitted\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-title\fP <title>: Document title\. Overrides H1 extracted from Markdown\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\fP <text>: Inline Markdown content\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\-file\fP <file>: Read Markdown content from a file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-\-key\fP <name>: Signing key name or account ID\.

.RE
.P
Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document create z6MkAccount \\
  \-\-path /blog/first\-post \\
  \-\-body\-file post\.md \\
  \-\-key mykey

seed\-cli document create z6MkAccount \\
  \-\-title "Quick Note" \\
  \-\-body "Hello **world**" \\
  \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.SS document update <id>
.P
Update an existing document's metadata, append content, replace content, or delete blocks\.
.P
The command fetches the current document state, computes the DAG depth from the change history, creates a new signed
.br
Change + Ref pair referencing the current heads as dependencies, and submits them to the server\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-title\fP <title>: Set document title\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-summary\fP <summary>: Set document summary\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\fP <text>: Markdown content to \fBappend\fR (inline)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\-file\fP <file>: Markdown content to \fBappend\fR from file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-replace\-body\fP <file>: Replace all document content with the Markdown in <file>\|\. Uses positional block matching to
.br
preserve block IDs where the block type at each position is unchanged\. This keeps block\-level comments and citations
.br
attached to their blocks when you edit content in place\. Cannot be combined with \fB\-\-body\fP, \fB\-\-body\-file\fP, or
.br
\fB\-\-delete\-blocks\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-parent\fP <blockId>: Parent block ID for appended content (default: document root)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-delete\-blocks\fP <ids>: Comma\-separated block IDs to delete\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-\-key\fP <name>: Signing key name or account ID\.

.RE
.P
Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
# Update title and summary
seed\-cli document update "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-title "New Title" \-\-summary "Updated" \-\-key mykey

# Append a new section
seed\-cli document update "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-body\-file new\-section\.md \-\-key mykey

# Full content replacement (preserves block IDs)
seed\-cli document update "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-replace\-body updated\-content\.md \-\-key mykey

# Delete specific blocks
seed\-cli document update "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-delete\-blocks "blockId1,blockId2" \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.SS document changes <targetId>
.P
List the change history (version DAG) of a document\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output \fBCID<tab>author\fP per line\.

.RE
.SS document stats <id>
.P
Get interaction statistics: citation count, comment count, change count, child document count, and per\-block
.br
citation/comment counts\.
.SS document cid <cid>
.P
Fetch and decode a raw IPFS block by its CID\.
.SS Comment Operations
.SS comment create <targetId>
.P
Create a comment on a document\. Comments are signed CBOR blobs posted to the target document's server\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\fP <text>: Comment text (inline)\. Supports inline mentions with the syntax \fB@[DisplayName](hm://accountId)\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-file\fP <path>: Read comment text from a file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-reply\fP <commentId>: Reply to an existing comment, creating a thread\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-\-key\fP <name>: Signing key name or account ID\.

.RE
.P
\fBBlock\-level comments\.\fR To anchor a comment to a specific block, include the block ID as a URL fragment in the target
.br
ID:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli comment create \\
  "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path?v=bafy\.\.\.#blockId" \\
  \-\-body "Comment on this block" \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
The CLI wraps the comment body in an Embed block whose \fBlink\fP field contains the full HM URL with the \fB#blockId\fP
.br
fragment\. This matches the behavior of the Seed desktop and web apps\.
.P
\fBInline mentions\.\fR Reference accounts in comment text using \fB@[DisplayName](hm://accountId)\fP:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli comment create "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-body "@[Julio](hm://z6MkJulio\.\.\.) check this out" \\
  \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
The display name is stripped during encoding; the account link is stored as an Embed annotation at the U+FFFC position
.br
in the text\. The mentioned account appears as a clickable link in the Seed desktop and web apps\.
.SS comment edit <commentId>
.P
Edit an existing comment\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-body\fP <text>: Updated comment text (inline)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-file\fP <path>: Read updated comment text from a file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-\-key\fP <name>: Signing key name or account ID\.

.RE
.P
The CLI preserves reply threading metadata for replies and keeps block-level anchor wrappers when editing comments that
.br
were originally attached to a specific block\.
.SS comment get <id>
.P
Fetch a single comment by its ID\.
.SS comment list <targetId>
.P
List all comments on a document\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output \fBcommentId<tab>authorName\fP per line\.

.RE
.SS comment discussions <targetId>
.P
List threaded discussions on a document\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-comment\fP <id>: Filter to a specific thread\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Minimal output\.

.RE
.SS Account Operations
.SS account get <uid>
.P
Get account information (name, icon, site URL)\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Print only the account name (or ID if unnamed)\.

.RE
.SS account list
.P
List all accounts known to the server\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output \fBhmId<tab>name\fP per line\.

.RE
.SS account contacts <uid>
.P
List contacts for an account\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Print names only\.

.RE
.SS account capabilities <id>
.P
List access control capabilities for a document or account\. Output includes capability ID, issuer, delegate, role, path,
.br
and recursion flag\.
.SS Search and Query
.SS search <query>
.P
Full\-text search across documents on the server\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-a\fP, \fB\-\-account\fP <uid>: Limit search to a specific account\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output \fBid<tab>title\fP per line\.

.RE
.SS query <space>
.P
List documents in a space (account) with filtering and sorting\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-p\fP, \fB\-\-path\fP <path>: Path prefix to filter\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-m\fP, \fB\-\-mode\fP <mode>: \fBChildren\fP (default) or \fBAllDescendants\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-l\fP, \fB\-\-limit\fP <n>: Maximum results\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-sort\fP <term>: Sort by: \fBPath\fP, \fBTitle\fP, \fBCreateTime\fP, \fBUpdateTime\fP, \fBDisplayTime\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-reverse\fP: Reverse sort order\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output \fBid<tab>name\fP per line\.

.RE
.SS children <space>
.P
Shorthand for \fBquery \-\-mode Children\fP\|\.
.SS citations <id>
.P
List documents that cite (link to) a given resource\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Output source IDs only\.

.RE
.SS Activity
.SS activity
.P
List recent activity events\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-l\fP, \fB\-\-limit\fP <n>: Page size\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-t\fP, \fB\-\-token\fP <token>: Pagination token (from previous response)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-authors\fP <uids>: Filter by author UIDs (comma\-separated)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-resource\fP <id>: Filter by resource HM ID\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP: Summary output only\.

.RE
.SS Key Management
.P
Keys are stored in the OS keyring, shared with the Seed desktop daemon\. Production keys use the \fBseed\-daemon\-main\fP
.br
keyring; development keys (\fB\-\-dev\fP) use \fBseed\-daemon\-dev\fP\|\.
.SS key generate
.P
Generate a new signing key from a BIP\-39 mnemonic\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-n\fP, \fB\-\-name\fP <name>: Key name (default: \fBdefault\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-w\fP, \fB\-\-words\fP <count>: Mnemonic word count: \fB12\fP or \fB24\fP (default: \fB12\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-passphrase\fP <pass>: Optional BIP\-39 passphrase for key derivation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-show\-mnemonic\fP: Display the generated mnemonic\. \fBSave it securely\.\fR

.RE
.SS key import <mnemonic>
.P
Import an existing key from a BIP\-39 mnemonic phrase\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-n\fP, \fB\-\-name\fP <name>: Key name (default: \fBimported\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-passphrase\fP <pass>: Optional BIP\-39 passphrase\.

.RE
.SS key list
.P
List all stored signing keys (name and account ID)\.
.SS key show [nameOrId]
.P
Show details for a specific key, or the default key if none given\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-show\-mnemonic\fP: Also display the mnemonic\. \fBHandle with care\.\fR

.RE
.SS key default [nameOrId]
.P
Set or show the default signing key\.
.SS key remove <nameOrId>
.P
Remove a stored key\. Requires \fB\-\-force\fP to confirm\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-f\fP, \fB\-\-force\fP: Skip confirmation prompt\.

.RE
.SS key derive <mnemonic>
.P
Derive and display the account ID from a mnemonic without storing the key\. Useful for verifying a mnemonic matches an
.br
expected account\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-passphrase\fP <pass>: Optional BIP\-39 passphrase\.

.RE
.SS key rename <nameOrId> <newName>
.P
Rename an existing key\.
.SS Configuration
.SS config
.P
Manage CLI configuration stored in \fB~/\.seed/config\.json\fP\|\.
.P
Options:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-server\fP <url>: Set default server URL\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-show\fP: Print current configuration\.

.RE
.SH WORKFLOWS
.SS Publishing a Markdown File as a New Document
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document create z6MkAccountUID \\
  \-\-path /blog/my\-post \\
  \-\-body\-file post\.md \\
  \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
The first H1 heading in the Markdown becomes the document title (override with \fB\-\-title\fP)\. The path is auto\-generated
.br
from the title if \fB\-\-path\fP is omitted\.
.SS Replacing Document Content
.P
To update all content in an existing document while preserving block IDs (so that block\-level comments and citations
.br
remain attached):
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document update "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-replace\-body updated\.md \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
The CLI matches new blocks to existing blocks by position and type\. Blocks at the same position with the same type reuse
.br
their existing ID and only emit a \fBReplaceBlock\fP if content changed\. New blocks get fresh IDs\. Blocks removed from the
.br
document are deleted\.
.SS Hierarchical Documents
.P
Documents form trees under an account\. The path determines hierarchy:
.RS 2
.nf
/                   home document
/projects           child of home
/projects/alpha     grandchild
.fi
.RE
.P
Create children by specifying deeper paths:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document create z6Mk\.\.\. \\
  \-\-path /projects/alpha \\
  \-\-body\-file alpha\.md \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
List children of a document:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli query z6Mk\.\.\. \-\-path projects \-\-mode Children \-q
.fi
.RE
.P
List all descendants recursively:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli query z6Mk\.\.\. \-\-mode AllDescendants \-q
.fi
.RE
.SS Block\-Level Comments

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
Find the target block ID\. Fetch the document as JSON and inspect the \fBcontent[]\.block\.id\fP fields:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \-\-json
.fi
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
Post the comment with the block ID as a URL fragment:
.P
seed\-cli comment create 
.br
"hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path?v=bafy\.\.\.#blockId" 
.br
\-\-body "My comment on this block" \-\-key mykey
.IP \(bu 2
Verify:
.P
seed\-cli comment list "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \-\-json

.RE
.SS Finding an Account by Name
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli account list \-s https://server\.com \-q | grep \-i horacio
.fi
.RE
.P
Or with JSON for exact matching:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli account list \-s https://server\.com \-\-json | \\
  jq '\.accounts[] | select(\.metadata\.name == "horacio") | \.id\.uid'
.fi
.RE
.SS Commenting with Mentions
.P
Reference another account in a comment:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli comment create "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-body "@[horacio](hm://z6MkHoracio\.\.\.) what do you think?" \\
  \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.P
The mention renders as a clickable account link in the Seed UI\.
.SS Replying to a Comment
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli comment create "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \\
  \-\-body "I agree" \\
  \-\-reply "z6MkAuthor\.\.\./z6FNCommentTsid" \\
  \-\-key mykey
.fi
.RE
.SS Exporting Documents as Markdown
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli query z6MkAccount \-\-mode AllDescendants \-q | \\
  while IFS=$'\\t' read \-r id name; do
    filename=$(echo "$name" | tr ' /' '_')
    seed\-cli document get "$id" \-\-md > "${filename}\.md"
  done
.fi
.RE
.SS Using a Different Server
.RS 2
.nf
# Per command
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\." \-s https://myserver\.com

# Set as default
seed\-cli config \-\-server https://myserver\.com
.fi
.RE
.SS CI/Automation with a Bot Key
.P
Import a key from a mnemonic stored in an environment variable:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli key import \-n bot "$BOT_MNEMONIC"
BOT_ID=$(seed\-cli key show bot \-q)
seed\-cli document update "hm://\.\.\." \\
  \-\-replace\-body content\.md \-\-key "$BOT_ID"
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSEED_SERVER\fP: Default server URL\. Overrides the built\-in default (\fBhttps://hyper\.media\fP) and the config file value\.
.br
The \fB\-\-server\fP flag takes precedence over this variable\.

.RE
.SH FILES

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB~/\.seed/config\.json\fP: CLI configuration (server URL, default account)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB~/\.seed/keys\.json\fP: Stored signing keys (mnemonics and derived account IDs)\. Created with mode \fB0600\fP (owner
.br
read/write only)\.

.RE
.SH KEYRINGS
.P
The CLI stores keys in OS keyrings shared with the Seed desktop daemon:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
Production: \fBseed\-daemon\-main\fP (default)
.IP \(bu 2
Development: \fBseed\-daemon\-dev\fP (with \fB\-\-dev\fP flag)

.RE
.P
Keys generated or imported in the CLI are immediately available to the desktop app and vice versa\.
.SH VERIFICATION
.P
Always verify writes by reading back:
.RS 2
.nf
seed\-cli document get "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \-\-md
seed\-cli comment list "hm://z6Mk\.\.\./path" \-\-json
.fi
.RE
.P
For automated pipelines, check exit codes: 0 = success, 1 = error\.
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"No signing keys found"\fR: No keys in the keyring\. Run \fBseed\-cli key generate\fP or \fBseed\-cli key import\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"Key not found: xyz"\fR: The specified key name or account ID doesn't exist\. Check \fBseed\-cli key list\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"API error (403)"\fR: The signing key lacks write permission on the target document\. The key must be the document
.br
owner or have a delegated capability (Writer or Editor role)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"No changes found for document"\fR: The Hypermedia ID doesn't match any known document on the server\. Verify the
.br
account ID, path, and server URL\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"Target is not\-found, expected a document"\fR: The document doesn't exist at the given HM ID\. Check path spelling and
.br
whether the document has been published\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB"API error (500)"\fR: Server\-side error\. Verify the server URL is correct and the server is running\. Try again; if
.br
persistent, check server logs\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBBlock IDs lost after update\fR: If you used \fB\-\-delete\-blocks\fP followed by \fB\-\-body\-file\fP, all blocks get new IDs\. Use
.br
\fB\-\-replace\-body\fP instead to preserve block IDs through positional matching\.

.RE
